    <!-- The test runs many concurrent memory-hungry `GROUP BY` queries under a
         tight 4 GiB container limit and asserts that the server survives (the
         final `SELECT 1` must succeed). The default
         `memory_worker_rss_speculative_reserve_ratio = 1.0` biases the observed
         RSS upward by the `resident - tracked` gap on every `MemoryWorker` tick.
         In the `amd_llvm_coverage` build (not a sanitizer build, so the
         speculation is not disabled at compile time) the coverage-instrumentation
         overhead inflates that gap, which keeps the biased `rss` above
         `max_server_memory_usage` even after the queries finish and makes the
         trailing `SELECT 1` fail with `MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`. The PR's mechanism
         is not under test here. -->
    <memory_worker_rss_speculative_reserve_ratio>0</memory_worker_rss_speculative_reserve_ratio>
</clickhouse>
